Here are several options to replace vodka in a pasta sauce:

1. White wine - This is the most common substitute and will add a similar depth of flavor
2. Chicken or vegetable broth - For a non-alcoholic option that still adds flavor
3. Water with a splash of white wine vinegar - This mimics the acidity without alcohol
4. Apple cider - Provides sweetness and acidity
5. White grape juice with a splash of vinegar - Another non-alcoholic option with balanced flavor
6. Lemon juice mixed with water - Adds brightness and acidity

The best choice depends on your preference for alcohol content and flavor profile. White wine is closest to the original recipe, while the broth or water-based options work well for alcohol-free alternatives.

